TEAM BEHIND AIDO























ARSHAD HISHAM




FOUNDER/CEO




Mr. Hisham is a serial entrepreneur and a Cranfield University (UK) MBA. He has built and run hardware automation companies. He has published research papers on Robotics and has held senior roles in the past at IBM, Govt. of Australia, and Toyota. Mr. Hisham is a frequent speaker on the Robotics most recently as a keynote speaker at the annual IEEE Robotics Symposium, Boston Consulting Group’s annual AI and machine learning event as well as at the industry-leading Robo-Business event among others.







TILBIN PAUL




INDUSTRIAL DESIGNER




An Innovative and effective industrial designer with expertise in coming up with radical and ground breaking designs in Human-Machine interfaces and machines including consumer products, transportation and automotive sector.







KARPAGARAJAN NATARAJAN




VP OPERATIONS




MBA with more than 10 years of experience in operations, and management in high growth companies.
He was the Turn around manager for a large organisation , where he managed more than 200 employees.









Sumeendranath R.




Software Engineering & AI




A Texas Instruments alumnus with more than 15 years experience of creating ground breaking technologies including a UNDP showcased project, complex electoral polling, GPS based data collection and state-of-the-art applications. Experience also involved developing AI/software for Soccer based Robots.







ANURAG PAL




CFO




Experienced finance professional with extensive operational, finance and sales and marketing background. Texas Austin MBA and previous roles include Director at Hewlett Packard.







Hareesh S




Hardware & Engineering




A hardware and electronics specialist with more than 15 years experience in development of machine control, firmware for special purpose machines, PLC programming., weapon simulators for the Army, control systems for truck driving simulators, and special purpose motors. Previous projects include Traab Engineering, Autoliv, Digicon, GKB Lenses, and, the Army.









Sabir A.




Mechanical Engineering




A Texas Instruments alumnus with more than 15 years experience of creating ground breaking technologies including a UNDP showcased project, complex electoral polling, GPS based data collection and state-of-the-art applications. Experience also involved developing AI/software for Soccer based Robots.










