Invest




$1.41 per share | $12M pre-money valuationBy investing now, you are betting that Aido will be worth more than $12M in the future.


































MISSION






Since day one, the goal of InGen Dynamics has been to build a useful, affordable and an advanced home robot . A beautifully crafted home robot that is a showpiece for robotic innovation. The next phase of the consumer robotics revolution is truly underway, and the next five years would set the stage for how these robots could fundamentally transform our homes and daily lives. We strongly believe that Aido will be a central part of this revolution and want to put an Aido in every home.






Key Facts






$900,000+ raised on Indiegogo and ranked #2 as one of the most successful home Robot campaigns of all timeRecipient of multiple awards including T3 Gamechanger of 2016Invited by Walt Disney to be showcased at their global innovation campusRecognized by major industry associations including IEEE, Boston Consulting Group, and Robo-Business Three functional prototypes complete and a functional SDK released to early developersFeatured in major global research reports on Security and Home Robotics






The Buzz About Aido















Meet Aido - the Next Generation Home Robot






Aido is an interactive personal home robot. He’s an all-in-one package that comes with the best of home automation, security, assistance, entertainment and much more. Smart, interactive, and uniquely mobile - Aido can play with your kids, help you with household chores, handle your schedule, and keep your home safe. 











































AN ENTERTAINER




Immerse yourself in your favorite movies and games with the interactive projector and speakers.















A HOME MAKER




Keep your home secure with Aido's patrol mode.  And keep your home healthy using his various sensors.















A TEACHER




Aido's sound effects, graphics, and movements make for an incredible interactive learning experience.



















A HELPER




Ask Aido to fetch the latest recipes, reschedule your meeting, or just dim the lights when you relax.















A HANDYMAN




Aido can quickly beam helpful videos on a nearby wall to fix that leaking faucet, or any faulty unit.















A FRIEND




Aido recognizes each member of your household, and adjusts to individual preferences.






































When our industrial designers were asked to start thinking about a new concept for a personal robot and home assistant, they turned to nature to garner inspiration. They were immediately attracted to dolphins.The dolphin's intelligence, playfulness, and friendliness, built-in smile, and merry-looking eyes have been a source of interest and enchantment to human beings for centuries. The senses of the dolphins have been subjected to intensive investigation, as have their intelligence and their remarkable systems of echolocation and communication.Dolphins also display culture, something long believed to be unique to humans. Dolphins also have a sleek, streamlined and attractive fusiform body. Aido's design principles draws its inspiration from Dolphins.








TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS



















Physical SpecificationTotal height:  914 mmTop height:  320 mmBottom height (w/o wheel):  554 mmNet weight:  8 Kg4 degree of motion ComputersCPU1: Quad Core ARM7 @ 1.6 GhzRAM: 1GB DDR3 RAMStorage: 32GB MicroSD CPU2: Quad Core ARM7 @ 1.6 GhzRAM:1GB DDR3 RAM CPU3: Dual-core A23 @ 1.5GhzRAM: 512MB GPU1: MaliMP2 GPU at 600 MHzGPU2: PowerVR SGX540 at 500MHzGPU3: MaliMP2 GPU at 600 Mz ConnectivityWiFi: 802.11b/g/nBluetooth: YesUSB:  5 external USB portProtocols: ZigBee, Z-Wave, WiFi and BLEUniversal IR Remote: Supports 1000+ Devices 






Sensors and InputsMicrophones:  6 Capsule Microphone ArrayGravity Sensor:  4-dimensional  G-sensorEnvironment Sensors: Temperature , Humidity,Ambient light , Air quality,  GPS, Noise, PressureCamera 1: 5 MP  cameraCamera 2: 1 MP 30 FPS Infrared visionCamera 3 & 4 (Tablet): 0.3 MP  Camera DisplaysProjector 1: Head mounted LED DLP (320x240)Projection:  0.2 - 2 Mts / 21’ ’  ( 10 Lumens )Projector 2: Body mounted LED DLP (640x480)Projection:  1- 3.5 Mts / 100’’ ( 100 Lumens ) Screen:  7” Touch Screen (800x400 ) SoftwareOperating Systems:  Android and LinuxCompatible with All Android AppsApps : House Maintenance, Kitchen Assistant, Medication and Health, and, Personal AssistantButler, Escort and Tag ModeTask AutomationWay points and Points of interestPatrol Paths /Escort PathsIndoor Mapping : WiFi and Object Recognition Based








Disclaimer: Aido is a work-in-progress and exact functionality and uses may be subject to change. Aido will have four points of contact for the mobilitymechanism and Aido does not balance on a single ball - the images above are for representational purposes only. We are still working through challenges on the mobility and home automation modules which are not yet functional.






































































Intellectual Property The Company is in the process of filing provisional patents on the hardware , mechanical engineering, and software components of Aido and plans to continue patent prosecution to completion.Hardware & SoftwareThere are four (4) main hardware components that are in the process of being patented with the possibility of further patentable parts: (1) Custom Daughterboard, (2) Microcontroller for Mobility, (3) Power Management Board and (4) IR, WIFI and Laser Based Docking.There are also four (4) main software components that are patentable: (1) Indoor Positioning, (2) Task Automation, (3) Linux Intelligence Wrapper, and (4)  Aido Speech EngineThere are 6 other mechanical engineering components and a design patent also under consideration.











GROWING FAST

















THE MARKET






Market Outlook






Market for consumer and business robots is forecast to explode in the next few yearsService Robotics market expected to grow from $5.6B in 2014 to $22.5B in 2021 at a 18.8% CAGR$1.5B market for consumer and business robots by 201917% CAGR between 2014 and 2019, three times faster growth than market for manufacturing robots Smartphones and Tablets have made it easier to develop robots for consumer and office space






Market Trends








Connected Home Devices: Forecast to grow at a CAGR of67% over the next 5 years with annual revenues to touch$490B by 2019Component Costs: Many of the sensor &component costs have declined by as much as 100X over the past decadeConsumer Adoption: 14M+ Roombas have been sold since launch; 4M+ in the last two years alone






31M personal use service robots forecast to be sold between 2014 and 2017. 




Sources: BI Intelligence, iRobot, Gigaom








Exit Strategy






We have received tremendous interest from leading electronics and home automation companies. Our goal is to build an extendable service and domestic robotic technology platform. We envision four potential exit scenarios: Sell the Platform,Company and the Brand value to a strategic buyer and investors can liquidate their sharesEvaluate an Initial Public Offering of securitiesMerge with any other automation integrator and pay investors dividends from profitsGrow organically and pay investors dividend from profits






