              Aido Home Robot Plays with Kids and Controls Smart Appliances
            


March 18, 2016


            Aido is a new personal robot that has turned up at Indiegogo and looks a bit like Wall-E’s girlfriend Eve if she were much taller and had a hunched back.
          











              This Is the Scariest Indiegogo Campaign You Will Ever See
            


May 7, 2016


            If you were already nervous about the A.I. revolution, there is a campaign on Indiegogo right now that will convince you to renounce all your worldly possessions and live forever in a southern Nevada commune. It’s called Aido, and it’s a rolling home robot—kind of like Siri if she became sentient and followed you around the house.
          











              This Friendly Robot Wants to Become Part of Your Family
            


August 27, 2016


            This friendly robot wants to become a part of your family. The Aido robot is a friendly, interactive home assistant that features voice activation, a multimedia projector, and smarthome control.
          











              Aido is pretty much the robot they promised everyone back in the 1950s
            


August 3, 2016


            Aido will be friends with your weird kid, act as a security guard, remember your schedule and project movies onto the wall to help with anything from cooking to plumbing. This is the robot to kill all robots. With kindness.
          











              Most Amazing Robots You Can Buy Now (Or Soon)
            


July 6, 2016


            With a 7-inch screen displaying expressive, animated eyes mounted on a rolling body, the Aido personal home robot differs from its competitors in three startling ways. First, Aido is a foot taller, making its stature a bit more comfortable for adults to deal with, whether you're asking it to dim the lights or it's patrolling your home on its own while you're away.
          











              Watch out Alexa, rivals are angling for your job
            


September 21, 2016


            How many job openings does your household currently have for robots or devices with artificial intelligence?

A California startup, Aido, is developing a $940 home robot that looks similar to Jibo but balances on a single rolling ball and can move around the house. (Jibo sits wherever you put it.) That lets Aido measure air quality as it moves around your home or serve as a security guard.
          











              The smart robots about to invade your home
            


June 24, 2016


            From the dreamy demo video it looks like Aido will be able to project your Facebook News Feed on the wall, teach your daughter piano, keep an eye on the cooking, integrate with other smart home devices and patrol the hallways when you've all gone to bed.
          

















